The paper focuses on modeling topics, citations, and topical authority in academic papers, which are all relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions using Latent Dirichlet Allocation (LDA), which is a popular topic modeling technique in natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses modeling author influence on citations, which could be relevant to deep learning (cs.DL) and social networks (cs.SI).
